    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5631/205a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-15T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. We exchanged desiderata<note n="9" xml:id="d474fn9">Not printed.</note> this
                    morning with van Breugel. We handed to him at the same time a set of the general
                        provisions<note n="9" xml:id="d474fn10">Not printed.</note> which we propose
                    for inclusion in the trade agreement. Similar copies were handed to van Breugel
                    some weeks ago. He seems to consider that they were handed to him in a sort of
                    personal way but he said that he had nevertheless sent copies to his Government.
                    Van Breugel was told that we would be glad to go forward with negotiations with
                    regard to the general provisions immediately if his Government was so inclined.
                    He had said that he could not indicate when negotiations in other respects might
                    be started until after his Government had received our list.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
